Make Ahead Turkey Gravy
  --Cook's Country

1 tbsp vegetable oil
Reserved turkey neck and giblets, minus the liver
1 onion, chopped
4 c low sodium chicken broth
2 c water
4 sprigs fresh thyme (can sub dried)
1 bay leaf
4 tbsp unsalted butter
6 tbsp ap flour

Heat oil in large saucepan over medium high heat and brown giblets and neck for 5 min. Add onion and cook until softened, ~3 min, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20 min. Turn heat to high, add broth and water, scape pan bottom, and bring to boil. Reduce heat to low, add herbs, and simmer for ~30 min, skimming as needed. Pour broth through fine mesh strainer. Discard solids. Broth can be made in advance and stored in the refrigerator for 2 days. Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat. Whisk in flour. Cook, whisking constantly, until honey colored and fragrant, ~4 min. Bring reserved broth to simmer and add to pan, a little at a time, whisking constantly. Simmer gravy, whisking occasionally, until thickened, ~5 min. Set aside, covered, until turkey is done. gravy can be refrigerated, covered, for 1 day. Scrape up bits in roasting pan and pour drippings into fat separator. Reheat gravy over medium heat until bubbling. Add defatted drippings and simmer for 2 min until gravy thickens. Season with salt and pepper. Serve.
